Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.56,0:00:04.48,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,M spotted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.56,0:00:06.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,His mobile's ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.23,0:00:10.57,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hello, this is Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.86,0:00:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Nihon Bridge Post Office, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.16,0:00:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.83,0:00:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man on the phone told me to pick up a package held at a post office.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.12,0:00:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in under five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.04,0:00:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me through, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.42,0:00:30.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M is heading south down Main Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.93,0:00:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm here to pick up a parcel being held.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure. Do you have any ID?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.78,0:01:03.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This case began five days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.62,0:01:06.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It doesn't matter how many times you try,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.75,0:01:08.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}whether it's in love, deductions, today, or tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.67,0:01:10.71,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The culprit chose the old man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.71,0:01:12.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A surprising case aboard a cherry blossom viewing boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.63,0:01:14.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.51,0:01:16.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.34,0:01:18.85,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.73,0:03:16.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Several employees of "New Image", an company\Nspecialising in importing and selling American cars,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.24,0:03:20.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}were attacked and severely injured in quick succession.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.12,0:03:27.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, New Image's president received\Na threatening call from the one responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.66,0:03:31.58,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}2.4 million yen?! You must be joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.34,0:03:37.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.46,0:03:41.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So, the case fits exactly 2.4 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.93,0:03:43.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.10,0:03:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.77,0:03:52.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was going to a department store with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} when I spotted Uncle Kogoro running about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.77,0:03:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s in the middle of a job, so don't disturb him, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.19,0:03:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.36,0:04:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Miwako! Were you waiting? Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.53,0:04:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Were you waiting"? Sheesh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.83,0:04:08.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, today's on you, right, Wataru?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.71,0:04:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It always is, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.54,0:04:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.83,0:04:14.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.92,0:04:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, we should get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.80,0:04:20.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.64,0:04:32.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Put the money in this briefcase."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.39,0:04:36.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Get rid of your mobile. I'll contact\Nyou through this transceiver."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.48,0:04:42.28,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Get on the 17:45 flower viewing\Ncruise departing from Nihon Bridge."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.28,0:04:44.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"Get rid of the microphone you're\Nusing to contact the police."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.08,0:04:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M is heading north, still on Main Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.87,0:04:51.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.58,0:04:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.54,0:04:55.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.25,0:04:57.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, it's a note Uncle discarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:04:59.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's part of his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.26,0:05:02.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks. Take care on your way home, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.26,0:05:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.01,0:05:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the culprit's instructions!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.60,0:05:10.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.56,0:05:15.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to a note from the criminal,\Nfuture contact will be through a transceiver,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.10,0:05:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and he told M to board a cruise departing from Nihon Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:21.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My bad! Sorry for making you wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.49,0:05:26.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you Ishida{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.16,0:05:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.53,0:05:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought you weren't going to show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.12,0:05:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.50,0:05:35.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.00,0:05:36.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've kept you all waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.71,0:05:39.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then, now that everyone's here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.29,0:05:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's depart!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.51,0:05:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boat M boarded just departed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.52,0:05:55.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.77,0:05:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boat that just left, that was\Nthe flower-viewing cruise, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.27,0:06:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where does it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.27,0:06:04.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is. It goes out of the Sumida River and into Ōyoko River.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.28,0:06:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you like a pamphlet?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.99,0:06:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.75,0:06:15.29,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.29,0:06:19.17,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I wonder why I was chosen to deliver the money?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.50,0:06:21.88,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We aren't entirely sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:24.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Don't you have any ideas yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.42,0:06:25.67,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:33.64,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He also said that he'd take a life if the police didn't\Nstay out of this, or if his demands weren't met.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.27,0:06:37.94,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've prepared the 2.4 million yen that guy demanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.94,0:06:39.52,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm leaving this case in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.19,0:06:42.73,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Our employees' lives can't be replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.73,0:06:43.65,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.40,0:06:46.74,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You can count on Kogoro Mouri!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.49,0:07:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In about 10 minutes, we'll be leaving the Sumida River,\Nso be careful not to fall off when the waves get rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.05,0:07:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.84,0:07:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, it's like in the movies!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.39,0:07:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seein' Tokyo by boat's great, ain't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.56,0:07:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It says here that the Sendaibori River ahead is called the Sendaibori because it was built by the old Sendai Domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.44,0:07:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.24,0:07:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cruise M is on just passed Minato Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.28,0:07:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The suspect will pick up the money somewhere along the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.83,0:07:35.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep your eyes peeled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.41,0:07:35.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.08,0:07:41.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A transceiver has a range of 100 meters at best.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.54,0:07:44.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The criminal must be somewhere within that range!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.54,0:07:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato, where are you right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.05,0:07:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're on standby just past Eitai Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.26,0:07:55.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've contacted the cruise company, and the boat's scheduled to enter Ōyoko River from Sumida River.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.31,0:07:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get ahead of it and wait for it at Ōyoko River.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.81,0:07:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.40,0:08:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.69,0:08:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.69,0:08:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about time to get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.49,0:08:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boat is about to pass the Ōshima River flood gates, and head into Ōyoko River.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.03,0:08:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it does, place the briefcase on the boat's roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.54,0:08:23.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put it right in the middle so it doesn't fall off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.04,0:08:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once that's done, sit down and await further instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.55,0:08:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, the boat's not shaking at all now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.14,0:08:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because the Ōyoko River is actually a canal.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.06,0:08:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The region's {\i1}daimyō{\i0} built it under orders of the shogunate{bakufu}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.12,0:08:56.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That brat...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.20,0:08:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't get in the way, brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.79,0:09:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lower your head!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.79,0:09:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was a shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.88,0:09:13.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At high tide, the water level rises so much that\Neven this boat has trouble getting under bridges.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.05,0:09:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.13,0:09:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, when you usually don't lower your head, it's a good experience to bow right down to someone once in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.01,0:09:20.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.85,0:09:22.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The briefcase is on the boat's roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.53,0:09:41.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He wouldn't be able to pull it up onto the\Nbridge when there's so many people about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.75,0:09:42.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Even more so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.67,0:09:50.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}When there's surveillence cameras dotted about.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.98,0:10:09.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you waiting?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.73,0:10:14.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That was close!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.55,0:10:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M has entered the Heikyū River.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:47.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The briefcase's on the boat's roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.73,0:10:50.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! Don't take your eyes off that boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.19,0:10:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.19,0:10:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go get the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.31,0:11:33.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The briefcase is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.57,0:11:42.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The briefcase is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.11,0:11:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, why're you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.45,0:11:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The briefcase is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.86,0:11:50.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.07,0:11:51.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! We've gotta tell the Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.62,0:11:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.04,0:11:59.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.25,0:12:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, bad news!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.38,0:12:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.21,0:12:04.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hush, you! Don't get in the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.00,0:12:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The briefcase's not on the roof!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.30,0:12:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.51,0:12:13.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's gone, gone, gone, gone, gone,\Ngone, gone, gone, gone, gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.31,0:12:15.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please be careful! That's dangerous!{lit. Please, customer!}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.81,0:12:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The briefcase vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.94,0:12:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.61,0:12:27.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.44,0:12:31.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How did the criminal get the briefcase\Nfrom all the way over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.00,0:12:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you received orders through a transceiver, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.46,0:12:49.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"When you reach Ōyoko River,\Nput the briefcase on the roof."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.13,0:12:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ye...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.80,0:12:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.35,0:12:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that the only contact you had?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.81,0:12:58.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.77,0:13:02.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And before you knew it, the briefcase was gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.23,0:13:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, they ordered me to sit down\Nand wait for the next order.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.03,0:13:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How humiliating.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.90,0:13:15.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, where did you last see the briefcase?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.41,0:13:16.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.99,0:13:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here! At Tōtomi Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.04,0:13:23.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We last saw it here, at Shiomi Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.63,0:13:30.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you realized the briefcase was gone\Nwhen you were here, at Hamazono Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.47,0:13:37.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the culprit must've taken it somewhere\Nbetween Heikyū Bridge and Hanazono Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.35,0:13:40.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, did you notice anything special?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.73,0:13:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry... I think I caught a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.61,0:13:49.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.69,0:13:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! Back then, I heard a sound\Nlike something hitting against metal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.62,0:13:56.99,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hitting against metal?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.99,0:14:00.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was somewhere around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.41,0:14:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was an ordinary, small bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.50,0:14:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were two rowboats moored under the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.21,0:14:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were there any people on them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.30,0:14:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.22,0:14:16.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boatman turned to the right to avoid those rowboats.\NThen, when we passed under the bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.47,0:14:19.22,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hmm? What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.85,0:14:21.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did you hit the bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.77,0:14:22.68,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.68,0:14:25.06,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I did, the boat'd be shaking more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.06,0:14:26.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.69,0:14:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably Shigure Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:37.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we looked over from Shiomi Bridge, we could see\NHeikyū Bridge, and there weren't any rowboats there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.62,0:14:42.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Ishihama Bridge, beyond Shigure\NBridge, has flood gates right behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.91,0:14:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't what you'd think of as "an ordinary, small bridge".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.00,0:14:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.34,0:14:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hamazono Bridge is straight after that, so I think\Nthat metal sound must've been at Shigure Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.84,0:15:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is that metal sound really connected with the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.06,0:15:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Megure!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.98,0:15:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was found floating in the river near Heikyū Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.52,0:15:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.98,0:15:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this is definitely the briefcase, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.90,0:15:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.61,0:15:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's open it up and check inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.99,0:15:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I watch too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.67,0:15:30.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.17,0:15:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cloth in the lid of this case is ripped!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.88,0:15:36.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.09,0:15:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, as Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} said, forensics reported\Nthat the lining in the lid had been torn out,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.76,0:15:46.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and there were traces that something\Nhad been planted inside the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.44,0:15:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the culprit took the case\Nusing whatever they put in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.15,0:15:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, they couldn't tell that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:15:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.11,0:16:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.70,0:16:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, this is a clue to how the briefcase was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.37,0:16:06.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.29,0:16:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Your voice is back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:09.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Whoops!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.13,0:16:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My flash of insight cleared out my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.00,0:16:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.13,0:16:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.63,0:16:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit used a powerful magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.43,0:16:20.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Magnet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.18,0:16:26.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One characteristic of Ōyoko River is that the water\Nlevel changes greatly with the tide's ebb and flow,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.23,0:16:29.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,greatly decreasing the space under the bridges.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.19,0:16:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator probably checked what time the water level rises beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.94,0:16:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and concealed a powerful magnet in the briefcase's lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.45,0:16:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when the cruise boat passes just under a bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.45,0:16:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on. There are so many bridges, the criminal wouldn't be able to tell which one it stuck to...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.83,0:16:59.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's why they used an electromagnet that would only magnetize when they needed it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.63,0:17:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An electromagnet created by wrapping a coil around a conductor\Nis only magnetic when electric current flows through the coil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.06,0:17:13.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit likely put magnetic cores with coils\Nwrapped around them and a battery into the lid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.86,0:17:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And to allow it to be activated remotely, they connected a remote switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.80,0:17:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when nobody was around, they\Nturned off the power, and retrieved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.72,0:17:55.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right. Based on your deduction, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, we'll\Nrecheck the area around Ōyoko River and Heikyū River.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.77,0:17:56.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.24,0:18:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.70,0:18:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you sleep here, you'll just make your cold worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.12,0:18:09.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder why the culprit chose Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.66,0:18:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.08,0:18:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You keep documents about the cases Uncle investigates, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.75,0:18:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think they're filed away over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.59,0:18:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe we could find out something\Nif we looked through them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.47,0:18:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't think the culprit is someone\Nwho holds a grudge against Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.53,0:18:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something wrong, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.57,0:18:48.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.54,0:18:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was just thinking that if Shin'ichi\Nwere here, he'd solve it in an instant.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.38,0:19:00.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. I'll solve it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.13,0:19:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you {\i1}are{\i0} part of the Detective Boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.51,0:19:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we'll solve the case together instead of Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.39,0:19:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.93,0:19:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key is New Image, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.43,0:19:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There must be some connection between Uncle and New Image.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.68,0:20:38.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.81,0:20:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Couldn't this be it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.35,0:20:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.19,0:20:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satoshi Nishizawa, 32 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.82,0:20:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mechanic and engineer for the\Nimport car company, New Image.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.82,0:20:57.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A client, Kaori Yoda, asked the old man to find\Nout the identity of the stalker following her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.95,0:21:01.54,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Through the investigation, the\Nstalker was found to be Nishizawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.54,0:21:07.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He received a court order to stay away from the client, and was dismissed from his job.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.67,0:21:10.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This case was two months ago, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.13,0:21:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's his address?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.72,0:21:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fukagawa, Kōtō district.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.64,0:21:15.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right near Ōyoko River!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.39,0:21:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.98,0:22:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.61,0:22:58.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the flat, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.53,0:22:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.12,0:23:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nishizawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, are you there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.42,0:23:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nishizawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.96,0:23:13.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like he's out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.01,0:23:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.31,0:23:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nishizawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.35,0:23:27.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nishizawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.02,0:23:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, stop, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.95,0:23:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you can't just\Nwalk into someone else's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.18,0:24:01.60,Dialogue,NEP,0,0,0,,While trying to find out what happened to the ransom,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.60,0:24:03.68,Dialogue,NEP,0,0,0,,the suspect was found dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.68,0:24:09.27,Dialogue,NEP,0,0,0,,On the next Conan: The Evening Cherry Blossom Viewing Route on Sumida River (Part II)!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.27,0:24:14.19,Dialogue,NCH,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Flower-viewing boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.19,0:24:15.69,Dialogue,Conte,0,0,0,,Dad, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.49,0:24:19.15,Signs,Conte,0,0,0,,hana
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.49,0:24:19.15,Signs,Conte,0,0,0,,hana
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.49,0:24:19.15,Dialogue,Conte,0,0,0,,No flowers{hana} in sight, but his nose{hana} is in full bloom.
